text: Swisscom AG is Switzerland’s leading telecommunications and information technology company. It offers a comprehensive range of services including mobile and fixed-line telephony, broadband internet, digital television, and various IT services. Headquartered in Ittigen, near Bern, Swisscom also has a significant presence in Italy through its subsidiary Fastweb. As of 2023, it employs approximately 19,729 full-time equivalents and reported revenues exceeding 11 billion CHF. The company plays a dominant role in the Swiss telecommunications sector, holding significant market shares in mobile communications, broadband internet, and digital television. Swisscom is recognized for its innovation and sustainability efforts, investing heavily in research and development and various sustainability initiatives.
